    <tags>pangolin cli wireguard zero-trust proxy remote-access ztna ssh automation tool</tags>
    <summary>Command-line client for Pangolin — authenticate, apply blueprints, and reach resources via identity-aware ssh/scp</summary>
    <description>Pangolin CLI is the official command-line client for [Pangolin](https://pangolin.net/) — an identity-aware, self-hostable tunneled reverse proxy and mesh VPN built on WireGuard. It works with both Pangolin Cloud and self-hosted Community/Enterprise servers.

On **Linux** the CLI is also the official way to bring up the Pangolin VPN tunnel. On **Windows** the WireGuard tunnel is handled by the separate GUI client, so here the CLI is the management and automation tool for Pangolin:

* Authenticate to Pangolin Cloud or a self-hosted server (`pangolin login` / `pangolin auth`)
* Apply configuration and blueprints as code (`pangolin apply`)
* List resources and show client status (`pangolin list`, `pangolin status`)
* Reach your resources with identity-aware `pangolin ssh` and `pangolin scp`
* Select the active context and self-update (`pangolin select`, `pangolin update`)

Note: the VPN tunnel commands (`up` / `down`) are Linux-only and are not available on Windows — use the Pangolin GUI client for the tunnel on Windows.

## Package notes

This package installs the official Windows MSI from the [fosrl/cli](https://github.com/fosrl/cli) GitHub releases and is maintained automatically. It is not affiliated with or endorsed by Fossorial, Inc.</description>
